name: FruitNumber
study: Adaptive diversification of growth allometry in the plant Arabidopsis thaliana
scoring: Total number of fruits per plant at the end of reproduction (fruit ripening).
growth_conditions: Growth chamber set at 16°C 12/12 h photperiod, under semi-hydroponic conditions.
eo_definition: "The treatment involving study type in which plants were grown in growth chambers." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of physical quantity consisting of only a numerical number without any units." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

name: RGR
study: Adaptive diversification of growth allometry in the plant Arabidopsis thaliana
scoring: Relative growth rate (mg d-1 g-1) measured at the inflection point of the growth curve (i.e. half final plant size), using image analysis and modelling.
growth_conditions: Growth chamber set at 16°C 12/12 h photperiod, under semi-hydroponic conditions.
to_name: shoot system growth and development trait
to_definition: "A plant structure growth and development trait (TO:0000928) that is a quality of the growth of the shoot system (PO:0009006), and shoot system development stages (PO:0025527)." [GR:pj, TO:cooperl]
eo_definition: "The treatment involving study type in which plants were grown in growth chambers." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of movement. Speed is measured in the same physical units of measurement as velocity, but does not contain the element of direction that velocity has. Speed is thus the magnitude component of velocity." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

name: rosetteDM
study: Adaptive diversification of growth allometry in the plant Arabidopsis thaliana
scoring: Rosette dry mass (mg) measured at the end of the life cycle, at fruit ripening
growth_conditions: Growth chamber set at 16°C 12/12 h photperiod, under semi-hydroponic conditions.
to_definition: "The dry weight of the whole plant." [GR:pj37]
eo_definition: "The treatment involving study type in which plants were grown in growth chambers." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gram or 10^[-3] g." [UOC:GVG]

uo_definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of movement. Speed is measured in the same physical units of measurement as velocity, but does not contain the element of direction that velocity has. Speed is thus the magnitude component of velocity." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]
